    "markdown": "---\nformat:\n  html:\n    css: styles.css\n    embed-resources: TRUE\n    code-fold: true\n    page-layout: full\n    fig_caption: yes\n---\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n\n\n::: narrow-section\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"grid-container\" style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); justify-items: center;\">\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">0</div>\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">0</div>\n<div style=\"display: block; &#10;              color: #3E4B4B; &#10;              font-size: 1.25em; &#10;              font-family: Graphik; &#10;              font-weight: bold; &#10;              text-align: center;\">NA</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">Currently Eligible<br>for Parole</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">Eligible for Parole<br>in the next 1-5 years</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">\n<span class=\"tippy html-widget html-fill-item-overflow-hidden html-fill-item\" height=\"338px\" id=\"htmlwidget-c7e9116fb7bd442924d3\" width=\"100%\"></span>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-c7e9116fb7bd442924d3\">{\"x\":{\"opts\":{\"placement\":\"bottom\",\"flip\":true,\"theme\":\"light\",\"content\":\"To compare the degrees of indeterminacy, or unpredictability\\n   of time served, of prison-sentencing systems of different jurisdictions,\\n   we use a qualitative ranking framework based on the Robina Institute's\\n   Prison-release Discretion And Prison Population Size Report.<br><br><b>Not Available<\\/b>: .\"},\"text\":\"<span aria-label=\\\"To compare the degrees of indeterminacy, or unpredictability\\n   of time served, of prison-sentencing systems of different jurisdictions,\\n   we use a qualitative ranking framework based on the Robina Institute's\\n   Prison-release Discretion And Prison Population Size Report.<br><br><b>Not Available<\\/b>: .\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" role=\\\"button\\\">Prison Sentencing<br>System&#9432;<\\/span>\"},\"evals\":[],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n:::\n<br><br>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n:::: {.panel-tabset .nav-pills}\n\n## Prison Population\n<center>\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">Admission Types</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">\nPrison populations are shaped by two primary groups: new court commitments, or individuals newly incarcerated for a criminal offense, and parole returns/revocations, those who return to prison for failing to meet the conditions of their parole.\n\n</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"visualization\">No Data. Michigan did not submit data to the National Corrections Reporting Program in 2020.</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"visualization\">No Data. Michigan did not submit data to the National Corrections Reporting Program in 2020.</div>\n<br/>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">Prison Population Trends</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">The graph below provides a decade-long perspective on the prison system in Michigan, highlighting three key metrics from 2010 to 2020. It showcases the overall prison population trend, comparing it with the number of individuals who were released from prison to parole, as well as those who met the eligibility criteria for parole but remained incarcerated.</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"visualization\">\n<div class=\"highchart html-widget html-fill-item-overflow-hidden html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-d697f21528cf53bf6fb7\" style=\"width:100%;height:500px;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-d697f21528cf53bf6fb7\">{\"x\":{\"hc_opts\":{\"chart\":{\"reflow\":true,\"marginBottom\":50},\"title\":{\"text\":\"Trends in Prison Population, Releases to Parole, and Parole Eligibility from 2010 to 2020\"},\"yAxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":null},\"labels\":{\"format\":\"{value:,.0f}\"}},\"credits\":{\"enabled\":true,\"text\":\"Source: NCRP Year End Population (2020), BJS Prisoners (2010-2020), and Annual Parole Survey (2010-2018). Parole-eligible populations only include people in prison for a new crime and with original sentence lengths of 1 to 25 years.\"},\"exporting\":{\"enabled\":true},\"boost\":{\"enabled\":false},\"plotOptions\":{\"series\":{\"label\":{\"enabled\":false},\"turboThreshold\":0},\"treemap\":{\"layoutAlgorithm\":\"squarified\"},\"column\":{\"dataLabels\":{\"enabled\":true}},\"accessibility\":{\"enabled\":true,\"keyboardNavigation\":{\"enabled\":true},\"linkedDescription\":\"This graph shows the change in the number of\\n                                  people in prison, number of people released from\\n                                  prison to parole, the number of people eligible\\n                                  for parole but in prison, from 2010 to 2020 in the state of Michigan.\",\"landmarkVerbosity\":\"one\"},\"area\":{\"accessibility\":{\"description\":\"This graph shows the change in the number of\\n                                  people in prison, number of people released from\\n                                  prison to parole, the number of people eligible\\n                                  for parole but in prison, from 2010 to 2020 in the state of Michigan.\"}}},\"xAxis\":{\"categories\":[2010,2011,2012,2013,2014,2015,2016,2017,2018],\"labels\":{\"format\":\"{value}\"}},\"series\":[{\"name\":\"Prison Population\",\"data\":[44113,42940,43636,43759,43390,40355,41122,39666,38761]},{\"name\":\"Released from Prison to Parole\",\"data\":[11359,10251,9019,9803,9481,9956,null,9588,8902]},{\"name\":\"Eligible for Parole but in Prison\",\"data\":[1573,1694,2234,3367,3451,3252,2781,2604,2440]}],\"tooltip\":{\"shared\":true,\"crosshairs\":true}},\"theme\":{\"colors\":[\"#ff6400\",\"#ffaf00\",\"#c376fb\",\"#003474\",\"#00aba0\",\"#0061e4\"],\"chart\":{\"style\":{\"fontFamily\":\"Graphik\",\"fontSize\":\"12px\",\"color\":\"#3E4B4B\"}},\"title\":{\"align\":\"center\",\"style\":{\"fontFami