\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">Sentence Length</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"visualization\">No Data. Michigan did not submit data to the National Corrections Reporting Program in 2020.</div>\n<div id=\"visualization\">No Data. Michigan did not submit data to the National Corrections Reporting Program in 2020.</div>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">Criminal Offense</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"visualization\">No Data. Michigan did not submit data to the National Corrections Reporting Program in 2020.</div>\n<div id=\"visualization\">No Data. Michigan did not submit data to the National Corrections Reporting Program in 2020.</div>\n<br/>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n</center>\n<br>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n## Parole Eligibility\n\n<center>\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">How is Parole Eligibility Determined?</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">A prisoner must serve the duration of the minimum term imposed by the sentencing court before becoming eligible for parole. If an inmate is serving consecutive sentences, the minimum terms are added together to form the total minimum to be served. Similarly, the maximum terms are added together to determine the maximum possible time to serve both sentences.</div>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">Parole-Eligible Prison Population</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">In 2020, there were NA people were eligible for parole but still in prison for new crimes and with original sentence lengths ranging from 1 to 25 years. This group made up NA% of the prison population.</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"bar-chart\">\n<div id=\"htmlwidget-6656f485a1b160a0988b\" style=\"width:100%;height:300px;\" class=\"highchart html-widget \"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-6656f485a1b160a0988b\">{\"x\":{\"hc_opts\":{\"chart\":{\"reflow\":true,\"height\":300,\"marginBottom\":50},\"title\":{\"text\":\"Prison Population by Parole Eligibility Status in 2020\"},\"yAxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"\"},\"type\":\"linear\",\"labels\":{\"format\":\"{value}%\",\"enabled\":false},\"min\":0,\"max\":1},\"credits\":{\"enabled\":true,\"text\":\"Source: NCRP Year End Population (2020). Note: Parole-eligible populations only include people in prison for a new crime and with original sentence lengths of 1 to 25 years.\"},\"exporting\":{\"enabled\":true},\"boost\":{\"enabled\":false},\"plotOptions\":{\"series\":{\"label\":{\"enabled\":false},\"turboThreshold\":0,\"showInLegend\":true,\"stacking\":\"normal\",\"animation\":false,\"cursor\":\"pointer\",\"borderWidth\":3,\"minPointLength\":4},\"treemap\":{\"layoutAlgorithm\":\"squarified\"},\"scatter\":{\"marker\":{\"symbol\":\"circle\"}},\"accessibility\":{\"enabled\":true,\"keyboardNavigation\":{\"enabled\":true},\"linkedDescription\":\"This graph shows the proportion of the prison population by parole eligibility status in 2020 in the state of Michigan. Parole eligibility statuses include the new crime popultion currently eligible,\\n      new crime population eligible in 1 to 5 years, new crime population eligible in 6 or more years, other population currently or\\n      eligible in the future, and population with missing parole eligibility data.\",\"landmarkVerbosity\":\"one\"},\"area\":{\"accessibility\":{\"description\":\"This graph shows the proportion of the prison population by parole eligibility status in 2020 in the state of Michigan. Parole eligibility statuses include the new crime popultion currently eligible,\\n      new crime population eligible in 1 to 5 years, new crime population eligible in 6 or more years, other population currently or\\n      eli