e. The RRI provides insight into the degree of overrepresentation or underrepresentation, with an RRI greater than 1 indicating that a particular racial or ethnic group is disproportionately represented. Source: BJS Prisoners (2020), Census (2020)</div>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"visualization\">\n<div class=\"highchart html-widget html-fill-item-overflow-hidden html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-fb89fc4782ccc3c8be41\" style=\"width:100%;height:500px;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-fb89fc4782ccc3c8be41\">{\"x\":{\"hc_opts\":{\"chart\":{\"reflow\":true},\"title\":{\"text\":\"People in the Community and in Prison, Parole-Eligible Prison Population, and Parole-Eligible People Released at First Opportunity by Race and Ethnicity in 2020\"},\"yAxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"\"},\"type\":\"linear\",\"labels\":{\"enabled\":false},\"min\":0,\"max\":1},\"credits\":{\"enabled\":true,\"text\":\"Source: NCRP Year End Population (2020) and Census (2020).\"},\"exporting\":{\"enabled\":true},\"boost\":{\"enabled\":false},\"plotOptions\":{\"series\":{\"label\":{\"enabled\":false},\"turboThreshold\":0,\"showInLegend\":true,\"animation\":false,\"cursor\":\"pointer\",\"borderWidth\":3,\"minPointLength\":4},\"treemap\":{\"layoutAlgorithm\":\"squarified\"},\"scatter\":{\"marker\":{\"symbol\":\"circle\"}},\"accessibility\":{\"enabled\":true,\"keyboardNavigation\":{\"enabled\":true},\"linkedDescription\":\"TBD accessibility text\",\"landmarkVerbosity\":\"one\"},\"area\":{\"accessibility\":{\"description\":\"TBD accessibility text\"}}},\"series\":[{\"name\":\"In the Community\",\"data\":[{\"state\":\"Michigan\",\"race\":\"Black, non-Hispanic\",\"n\":1031144,\"prop\":0.1302837464221195,\"prop_label\":\"13%\",\"n_label\":1031144,\"population_type\":\"In the Community\",\"tooltip\":\"<b>Michigan<\\/b><br><br><b>Black, non-Hispanic<\\/b><br><br><b>In the Community<\\/b><br><br>Percentage of People: <b>13%<\\/b>\",\"y\":0.1302837464221195,\"name\":\"Black, no